Definition: adjusted or located in relation to surroundings or circumstances
Example: sometimes used in combination; the house had its large windows oriented toward the ocean view; helping freshmen become oriented to college life; the book is value-oriented throughout
Synonyms: UNORIENTED, orientated, ORIENTING, adjusted, or, located, in, relation, to, surroundings, circumstances, sometimes, used, combination, the, house, had, its, large, windows, oriented, toward, ocean, view, helping, freshmen, become, college, life, book, is, value-oriented, throughout
Category: adj.all
